Here's a simple HTML file that creates a taskboard with a glass effect. Each task pane includes a title, description, reward, and a checkbox. The CSS is embedded for styling, and JavaScript is included for basic functionality.

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Taskboard</title>
    <style>
        body {
            font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
            background: linear-gradient(to right, #6a11cb, #2575fc);
            display: flex;
            justify-content: center;
            align-items: center;
            height: 100vh;
            margin: 0;
        }
        .taskboard {
            display: grid;
            grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(300px, 1fr));
            gap: 20px;
            padding: 20px;
            max-width: 1200px;
            width: 100%;
        }
        .task {
            background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.1);
            backdrop-filter: blur(10px);
            border-radius: 10px;
            padding: 20px;
            box-shadow: 0 4px 20px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.2);
            color: white;
        }
        .task h3 {
            margin: 0 0 10px;
        }
        .task p {
            margin: 0 0 10px;
        }
        .task .reward {
            font-weight: bold;
        }
        .task input[type="checkbox"] {
            margin-right: 10px;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <div class="taskboard">
        <div class="task">
            <h3>Task 1</h3>
            <p>Description of Task 1</p>
            <p class="reward">Reward: 100 Points</p>
            <label>
                <input type="checkbox"> Completed
            </label>
        </div>
        <div class="task">
            <h3>Task 2</h3>
            <p>Description of Task 2</p>
            <p class="reward">Reward: 200 Points</p>
            <label>
                <input type="checkbox"> Completed
            </label>
        </div>
        <div class="task">
            <h3>Task 3</h3>
            <p>Description of Task 3</p>
            <p class="reward">Reward: 150 Points</p>
            <label>
                <input type="checkbox"> Completed
            </label>
        </div>
        <div class="task">
            <h3>Task 4</h3>
            <p>Description of Task 4</p>
            <p class="reward">Reward: 250 Points</p>
            <label>
                <input type="checkbox"> Completed
            </label>
        </div>
    </div>
    <script>
        // JavaScript can be added here for additional functionality if needed
    </script>
</body>
</html>
```

### Explanation:
- The HTML structure includes a `div` for the taskboard and multiple task panes.
- Each task pane has a title, description, reward, and a checkbox.
- The CSS styles create a glass effect using a semi-transparent background and a blur effect.
- The layout is responsive, using CSS Grid to arrange the task panes. 

You can copy and paste this code into an HTML file and open it in a web browser to see the taskboard in action.

